The second Nikko is the N.T.S. (Nikko trap shotgun). 29" rib vent barrels both full choke. This gun is absolutely incredible. Tiger stiped stock and forearm, engraving on absolutely very portion and jeweling on internals to include extractors. Although the 512 was made where the Winchester 101's were this is essentially is a 101 with better wood and parts. Looking online there isn't another one for sale period. This is truely a collector piece and quite rare. 

Neither gun has import marks making them early models. 512 is from early 70's and N.T.S. Most likely from early 60's from research but it's tough as the Nikko company did not keep the same records other companies and the factory was demolished in the early 80's. 

I will gladly meet someone to take a look at either shotgun and send plenty of pictures upon request

There is someone who is posting pictures of nice firearms from other gun sites as his own. Most of these ads do not select a city, and it always asks to be contacted via e-mail directly. Now they are posting for close to the gun's value.

BEWARE THEY ARE EVERYWHERE!!!!

Putting aside religious and moral considerations if we allow a state to discriminate against individuals merely trying to exercise their Constitutional Rights as guaranteed by the Founding Fathers we leave the door open to all kinds of badness. If they can discriminate against you because of what you do in bed in your own home, they can definitely discriminate against you because of what you do at the range. Please sign this petition and help to preserve our Constitutional Rights as a whole, not just the bits and pieces certain religions decide they're okay with. The link is below.

http://www.change.org/petitions/gov-janice-brewer-veto-sb-1062


WILL TRADE FOR:

Life, Liberty, The Pursuit of Happiness, Separation of Church and State, Freedom of Religion, Freedom of Speech.
